attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64 (stripped to external PDB), for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, No line numbers, No symbols, Large address aware, No debug

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary functions as a sophisticated loader/stager. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) Payload Decryption: sub_401595 implements an XOR-based decryption loop to unpack a payload into a VirtualAllocated buffer. 2) Manual Import Resolution: sub_401563 manually resolves GetModuleHandleA and GetProcAddress within the allocated payload, a common technique to bypass static analysis. 3) Execution: The decrypted payload is executed by changing memory protections to PAGE_EXECUTE_READ and calling CreateThread. 4) Evasion/IPC: The sample uses internal named pipes (\\.\pipe\MSSE-%d-server) via CreateNamedPipeA and CreateFileA to transfer data between threads. 5) Section Manipulation: sub_401dc0 contains logic to manually remap and modify PE section protections to PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE, characteristic of advanced packers or self-modifying malware.
